    "recap_headline": "University of Richmond Athletics",
    "recap_text": "RICHMOND, Va. \u2013\nThe Richmond Baseball team collected a 19-1 victory over Coppin State in seven innings Tuesday at a sun-drenched Pitt Field.\nRichmond, 10-7 on the season, closes out a 12-game home stand this weekend when Saint Joseph's heads south to open Atlantic 10 Conference action at Pitt Field. First pitch is set for 1 p.m. for all three games. Friday's and Sunday's games will be streamed on ESPN+.\nAngel Santiago-Cruz\ncollected his first win of the season after tossing two scoreless frames and working around two hits and striking out three.\nSam Young\n,\nAaron Van Tuyle\n,\nChase Lawley\nfollowed with scoreless frames of their own.\nChristian Dray\nwent one and a third, allowing the Eagles only run of the day on a hit, a walk and a hit batter with two strikeouts. Paul Wiktop got the final two outs, including a strikeout.\nThe Spiders batted around in the first inning, scoring five runs on one hit, two hit batters, four walks and CSU error. UR was plunked a season-high eight times, including\nEvan Wilson\ngetting hit three times.\nMichael Elko\npaced the Spiders with a 3-for-3 day, including a double and a walk, scored four times and stole a season-high four bases.\nGrant Kennedy\ntallied two hits and two RBI and a walk while\nNoah Harvey\nchipped in his first two collegiate hits, including a two-RBI base hit in the fifth.\nIn the second inning, UR had six batters reach and three more runs score before the first out was recorded. Kennedy picked up one of his two RBI in the third on a double before\nTrevor Dosenbach\npushed a run in on a base hit.\nAfter two straight hit batters, UR had three-straight hits, including two doubles to push three more runs across in the fourth inning. Three more runs came in on four hits and two walks in the fifth for the Spiders. With two outs in the sixth, UR strung together, three walks, an infield single and a hit batter to push in three more runs."
  },
